Mm-hmm. Well,
I like to breathe unassisted.

252
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,398
- Oh, really?
- Mmm.

253
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:40,193
I thought you liked it
when I give you mouth to mouth.

254
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:11,629
State your business.

255
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:14,471
You're gonna shoot
an FBI agent, Burdett?

256
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,511
All I see is an intruder...

257
00:16:17,520 --> 00:16:19,829
...who just swallowed $80 worth
of my whiskey.

258
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:23,633
Put down the weapon.

259
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:25,113
Don't make me shoot you again.

260
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:26,795
Again?

261
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,592
Is that the way we're gonna play it?

262
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:35,190
What are you doing
in my house, Agent Lloyd?

263
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:38,039
Sitting, drinking, eating chocolate.

264
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:40,913
- You have a warrant?
- FBI doesn't have jurisdiction here.

265
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,439
I know, that's why I came down here.

266
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:43,993
Oh, I don't think it is.

267
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:47,157
The <i>Seven Seas Navigator</i>
docking here for a solid week.

268
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:50,033
They're having a nice promotion
for the maiden voyage,

269
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:52,754
calling it the Diamond Cruise.

270
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:55,713
A gem exhibit whose star attraction is

271
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,831
the third Napoleon Diamond.

272
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,190
Stop me when I get to the part
you don't know.

273
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,436
It's the only one you two haven't stolen.

274
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:03,515
Allegedly.

275
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:06,108
And it's gonna be right here
for a whole week-- the last of the set--

276
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:08,435
and I suspect you plan to purloin it.

277
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:09,549
Well, I don't.

278
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:11,398
So finish your drink and get out.

279
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:12,919
It's okay to be happy to see me.

280
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:15,998
Just because you're English doesn't
mean you need to hide your emotions.

281
00:17:16,120 --> 00:17:17,997
I'm Irish.
We let people know how we feel.

282
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:19,394
Now fuck off.

283
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,760
And you can take any bugs you planted
along with you.

284
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,353
I'm retired.

285
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:29,392
A retired guy wouldn't have anything
to worry about from those.

286
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:30,873
- Mind if I borrow this?
- Take it.

287
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,479
You might learn something from it.

288
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,238
But return it for me.
It's overdue.

289
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,998
Give my love to Lola, will you?

290
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,553
How was the tennis lesson?

291
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:51,399
Great. The teacher says I'm a natural.

292
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:54,159
He says I've got the best backside
he's ever seen.

293
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:55,235
That's <i>backhand</i>.

294
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:56,395
Don't go in there.

295
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:58,556
- Why?
- Let's talk.

296
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:03,076
Okay, you're making me nervous,
and I don't get nervous.

297
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:06,512
Agent Lloyd just left.

298
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:08,198
What's <i>he</i> doing here?

299
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:09,719
He came to show me this.

300
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:17,835
Damn it, Max.

301
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:19,359
Is this what we're here for?

302
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:21,835
No. It's not.

303
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:26,196
This is not retirement at all.

304
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:28,595
This is the next setup, isn't it?

305
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:31,518
Babe, <i>you</i> chose
this island, remember?

306
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:36,029
I hope you don't think
this is a gift from God.

307
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:39,550
'Cause this is God messing with us.

308
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:46,111
Oh, no. Max.

309
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,592
Did Stan do this?

310
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,392
Sort of.

311
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:53,874
I figured he'd bug the place,
so I started checking.

312
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,797
Did you find any?

313
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:58,036
Only what he wanted me to find.

314
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,598
There's another one here somewhere.

315
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:04,439
Now, don't worry.
I already checked.

316
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:05,675
There's nothing in there.

317
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,199
That's the problem.

318
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:08,833
There's nothing in here.

319
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:14,793
What is it?
What's wrong?

320
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:17,354
I hid the bullet in the camera.

321
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:18,993
What bullet?

322
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:21,190
The one he shot you with.

323
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,753
Oh, no.

324
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:27,157
I kept it to remind me
of how close I came to losing you.

325
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,635
Lola, you know that bullet
puts me on the scene.

326
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:32,320
I know, I know. I'm sorry.

327
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:34,317
I'll get it back.

328
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:51,828
Good morning, Mr. Lloyd.
Your suite is ready.

329
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,110
- Suite?
- Suite, sir.

330
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:56,037
It's a larger room.

331
00:19:57,440 --> 00:20:01,513
Atlantis reserves this bridge suite
for our more dignified guests.

332
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:07,638
Breakfast is on the house, these are
vouchers for free tennis lessons,

333
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:11,469
complimentary skin exfoliant,
seaweed body wrap and facial scrub,

334
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:14,068
located in the spa on the club level.

335
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:15,519
Also, please remember.

336
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:20,191
Shoes and shirt are required
in all public spaces at all times.

337
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:51,995
State your business.

338
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:54,998
You can't bribe me
with a seaweed body wrap, Max.

339
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,633
This doesn't buy you one bit of space.

340
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,716
I'm gonna be on you wherever you go.

341
00:20:58,840 --> 00:20:59,875
It's no bribe, Stanley.

342
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,230
I just want you to see
that if you lead the kind of life I do,

343
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:04,396
stealing is the last thing on your mind.

344
00:21:06,760 --> 00:21:08,159
Mr. Lloyd.

345
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:10,191
Are you ready for your massage?

346
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,238
I'll do your back.

347
00:21:13,360 --> 00:21:15,112
I'll do your front.

348
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:17,673
You son of a bitch.

349
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:28,872
- Lola?
- Yeah.

350
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:33,238
- He hid it in a black jewelry box.
- Good job.

351
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:34,554
Thank you.

352
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:36,432
Talented masseuse.

353
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:38,349
You get rid of it this time.

354
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,879
I will.

355
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:42,517
Good evening.
May I take your order?

356
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:46,391
No, thank you.
I just lost my appetite.

357
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:47,635
Just as well.

358
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:50,399
I don't take orders from criminals,
I arrest them.

359
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:51,953
Or fall asleep trying.

360
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:54,118
So you're admitting you were there.

361
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:57,038
No. I read about it in the papers,
just like everyone else.

362
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,991
You're famous.

363
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,273
I'm a punchline.

364
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:05,833
But like my grandma used to say,
he who laughs last laughs loudest.

365
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,598
By the way,
return that movie, would you?

366
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,199
The store called.

367
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:10,912
I haven't finished it yet.

368
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:13,998
They catch the thief,
but it's not who you think it is.

369
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:15,951
I don't like those twist endings.

370
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:17,399
Well, we don't like you.

371
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:20,114
- Aw.
- Lola.

372
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:23,153
They're playing your song.

373
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:26,078
Why don't you take Stanley
for a dance?

374
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,679
He's feeling lonely.

375
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:30,268
And I am feeling charitable.

376
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:32,513
Let's go, Stan.

377
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:33,675
Really?

378
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:37,156
I'll try to have her back by dawn.

379
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,275
Constable...

380
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:55,388
Can I help you?

381
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:57,238
I wanna talk to Mooré.

382
00:22:57,360 --> 00:22:58,554
Get out of the way.

383
00:22:58,680 --> 00:23:01,353
Monsieur Mooré is currently socializing.

384
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:04,233
Interrupting a man's leisure
is harassment.

385
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:06,555
That's not harassment.

386
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:09,114
You feel that?

387
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:11,356
- Ooh.
- That's harassment.

388
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:15,393
And you tell your boss
this is just the beginning.

389
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:18,637
I have two hands,
and I can't be bought.

390
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:19,715
Ooh.

391
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:26,114
Excuse me, constable.
May I have a word with you?

392
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:38,036
<i>Audrey, where you get that sugar?</i>

393
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:40,116
Listen, Stan,
I know what you're doing.

394
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:44,074
But if you drag Max into your game,
he will not lose.

395
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:46,111
Eventually, they all lose.

396
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:47,719
Not my Max.

397
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:50,115
Do yourself a favor--
leave us alone.

398
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:53,994
We're just a couple of retirees
trying to enjoy the island life.

399
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:57,396
All the same, I'll stick around,
see what develops.

400
00:23:58,880 --> 00:23:59,995
Excuse me.

401
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:01,678
In a second, honey.
You'll get your chance.

402
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:04,439
Damn, I got the stink on me tonight.

403
00:24:04,560 --> 00:24:06,152
Step off the dance floor, sir.

404
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:08,313
Hey!

405
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:10,032
- Have fun, Stan.
- Hey. Lola!

406
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:12,594
Police.
Raise your hands, sir.

407
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:16,194
I'm law.
Federal B.I.?

408
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:26,679
It is illegal on this island to carry
a concealed weapon without a permit.

409
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:28,358
I'm working a suspect.

410
00:24:31,320 --> 00:24:33,880
Are you not supposed to inform
local authorities when you arrive,

411
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:36,355
Agent Stanley P. Lloyd?

412
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:41,596
- You know him?
- He's my suspect.

413
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:44,632
Well, we're still gonna have to
take this to the station and register it.

414
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:46,034
You're letting the criminal go.

415
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:47,275
This is crazy.

416
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,833
You think this is crazy?

417
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:51,599
Your dancing, <i>that</i> was crazy.

418
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:53,153
This way, Agent Lloyd.

419
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:55,111
Welcome to paradise.

420
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:01,114
Okay.

421
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:03,993
- The watermarks and holograms match.
- Oh.

422
00:25:04,120 --> 00:25:06,076
But I still have to register the gun.

423
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:13,119
You have a nice smile.

424
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,912
I haven't smiled at you.

425
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:16,519
You will.

426
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:21,309
That's just the way I feel about it,
and they have to deal with it.

427
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:22,509
Yes, sir.

428
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:24,392
Ah, Sophie.

429
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:26,238
I need to speak to you.

430
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:28,794
I'm getting complaints
about you bothering Henri Mooré.

431
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:30,751
Just doing my job, Zacharias.

432
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:32,791
The man is practically
the unofficial mayor of the island.

433
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,433
In one year, he's made
everyone here like him,

434
00:25:34,560 --> 00:25:36,278
something you haven't been
able to do in a lifetime.

435
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:38,994
I guess we can't all be
the kiss-ass politician you are.

436
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:42,553
I want you to stay behind tonight
so we can discuss your attitude.

437
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:44,193
You knew about my attitude
the day we got married

438
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:45,719
and knew about it
the day we got divorced.

439
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:48,479
You're not gonna learn
any more about it tonight.

440
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:52,309
Besides, I have plans
with Special Agent Lloyd of the FBI.

441
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:54,351
He's just arrived on the island.

442
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:56,109
Is that so?

443
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:57,955
Shall we?

444
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:59,593
We shall.

445
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,832
She's feisty.

446
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:14,076
Mmm. Isn't it beautiful?

447
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:16,509
Yeah.

448
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:20,278
Is it enough?

449
00:26:21,040 --> 00:26:22,155
Of course it is.

450
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:37,711
Some people say the only way
to rid yourself of temptation

451
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:39,831
is to yield to it.

452
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:43,552
I don't know about that.

453
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:50,355
I say turn your back on temptation...

454
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:56,154
...or substitute something
more tempting.

455
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:12,075
See how easy that was?

456
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:23,235
What's the shortest amount of time
you've ever known a guy

457
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:26,670
before you kissed him?

458
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:29,959
I see what you're thinking,
and you can forget it.

459
00:27:30,080 --> 00:27:33,755
Guys come down to this island looking
for a slice of paradise with a local girl,

460
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:36,030
and they will say anything to get it.

461
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:39,628
I resent being lumped in with all guys,

462
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:42,797
though, admittedly,
I would say anything right now.

463
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:45,036
How long have you been chasing Max?

464
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:50,794
Seven years-- ever since the first
Napoleon Diamond went missing.

465
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:53,798
I got to the scene,
took a few shots at the getaway car.

466
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:58,357
Next day, bottle of champagne arrives
at FBI Headquarters for me,

467
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:02,996
with a note says,
"Aim for the tires next time."

468
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,678
He was baiting you.

469
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:07,553
- Hmm.
- Is there a money trail?

470
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:10,513
Everything's plain--
taxes, bank accounts.

471
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:13,677
He doesn't buy
expensive paintings, yachts, nothing.

472
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:18,590
I think it's more about the challenge
and the alibi-- that's his work of art.

473
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,392
Sounds like you admire him.

474
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:24,790
Would I like to live one day
in his velvety slippers?

475
00:28:24,920 --> 00:28:26,239
Maybe.

476
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:28,112
But I don't admire him.

477
00:28:28,240 --> 00:28:30,117
He's beat me too many times for that.

478
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:32,276
Maybe you need the female touch.

479
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:35,717
That's exactly what I need.

480
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:39,150
Listen, I want a big arrest,
you need local help.

481
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,475
I'll extend the FBI courtesy on this one.

482
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:43,795
As long as I'm riding shotgun.

483
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:52,395
What's going on?

484
00:28:52,520 --> 00:28:54,476
I'm expanding the deck.

485
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:56,113
You're trying to stay busy.

486
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:59,232
Look, on this deck,
we are going to sit here

487
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:02,158
and watch sunsets until we get old.

488
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:04,439
Can't wait.

489
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:05,913
Where are you going?

490
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:07,598
You said I need a hobby.

491
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,551
I guess I'll go find one.

492
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:10,635
Really?

493
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:12,671
I'll call you later.

494
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:42,989
He's here.

495
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:52,396
The centerpiece of our exhibit.

496
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:55,751
Napoleon had three priceless diamonds
set into the hilt of his sword.

497
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:58,838
After his defeat, they were pried out
and dispersed around the globe.

498
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:02,669
This is one of the rare occasions the last
remaining diamond is on public display.

499
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:05,268
And next, we have
some rare Egyptian gems.

500
00:30:32,840 --> 00:30:34,353
Cute little rock.

501
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,072
I'm just here to look.

502
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,235
Just as well.

503
00:30:37,360 --> 00:30:40,477
With six cameras--
four stationary, two revolving,

504
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:42,192
a dozen I.R. motion sensors--

505
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,834
Sixteen.
You missed the ones at ankle level.

506
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:47,269
Plus your standard
24-hour rotating guards.

507
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:49,755
Unbreakable polycarbonate display,

508
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:52,519
controlled by an uncopyable
magnetic key card.

509
