01:05:41,880 --> 01:05:42,915
Exactly.

1016
01:05:43,040 --> 01:05:45,235
Hell, I could
make her understand.

1017
01:05:51,880 --> 01:05:54,758
Max can't eat, can't sleep.

1018
01:05:54,880 --> 01:05:56,711
He's like an injured bird.

1019
01:05:56,840 --> 01:05:58,990
Stan's hurt.
He's in pain.

1020
01:05:59,120 --> 01:06:00,758
He's like a wounded dog.

1021
01:06:00,880 --> 01:06:03,440
He needs you, Lola.
You're his better half.

1022
01:06:03,560 --> 01:06:04,754
Just give him one more chance.

1023
01:06:04,880 --> 01:06:06,677
He's a good guy, Sophie.

1024
01:06:06,800 --> 01:06:09,951
I'm sure he's a liar,
but that comes with the job.

1025
01:06:10,960 --> 01:06:13,633
I don't know.
This is all a bit strange.

1026
01:06:13,760 --> 01:06:15,398
What do you think, Lola?

1027
01:06:15,520 --> 01:06:17,795
- I don't buy a word of it.
- I'm with you.

1028
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:19,194
- No, no, no.
- Hey, hey, hey.

1029
01:06:19,320 --> 01:06:20,435
- Listen, hear us out.
- Come on, one second.

1030
01:06:20,560 --> 01:06:21,515
Look...

1031
01:06:23,600 --> 01:06:26,068
Tonight the lies stop.

1032
01:06:26,200 --> 01:06:27,599
He's serious. It's over.

1033
01:06:27,720 --> 01:06:30,234
He's not chasin' it,
and I'm not chasin' him.

1034
01:06:30,360 --> 01:06:33,670
I'm sorry, but I won't believe you
until that ship is gone.

1035
01:06:33,800 --> 01:06:35,756
And we still got a few hours
before she sails.

1036
01:06:35,880 --> 01:06:37,916
Look, I can't make
that ship disappear tonight,

1037
01:06:38,040 --> 01:06:39,234
but I can make us disappear.

1038
01:06:39,360 --> 01:06:42,557
- What are you talking about?
- I found a hobby.

1039
01:06:44,480 --> 01:06:46,152
Wait a minute.
You didn't tell me about this.

1040
01:06:46,280 --> 01:06:47,998
When we come up for air,

1041
01:06:48,120 --> 01:06:51,749
that ship will be headed to Paris
and the diamond will be gone forever.

1042
01:07:13,400 --> 01:07:15,152
So, where you taking us?

1043
01:07:15,280 --> 01:07:17,350
We're headed to a hidden reef
where there's rumored to be

1044
01:07:17,480 --> 01:07:19,755
100 million in gold
somewhere among the wreckage.

1045
01:07:20,680 --> 01:07:21,829
You're kidding.

1046
01:07:25,040 --> 01:07:25,995
Wow!

1047
01:07:26,120 --> 01:07:27,758
Look at this.

1048
01:07:27,880 --> 01:07:30,792
Yeah, these ships have
been down here since the '40s,

1049
01:07:30,920 --> 01:07:33,115
but nobody's ever
found any gold.

1050
01:07:33,240 --> 01:07:35,959
Well, maybe with the help
of the FBI we'll get lucky.

1051
01:07:37,080 --> 01:07:38,798
My money's on Max.

1052
01:07:38,920 --> 01:07:42,674
100 million four ways--
that's 25 million apiece if we split it.

1053
01:07:46,920 --> 01:07:49,115
Have any idea where to start?

1054
01:07:49,240 --> 01:07:52,710
It could be anywhere down here.
Let's split up, look around.

1055
01:07:54,480 --> 01:07:58,553
You guys sure this is safe?
I'm allergic to shellfish.

1056
01:07:58,680 --> 01:08:02,116
You've got nothing to worry about.
I've seen how you handle sharks.

1057
01:08:29,360 --> 01:08:32,716
When we get back,
I'm buying everyone umbrella drinks.

1058
01:08:39,440 --> 01:08:43,035
Hey, little guy,
have you seen any gold down here?

1059
01:08:50,440 --> 01:08:53,910
Hey, Max, I'm counting on you
to make me a rich man.

1060
01:09:33,680 --> 01:09:36,240
Lola, hypothetically speaking,

1061
01:09:36,360 --> 01:09:38,999
what's it like to hold
25 million in your hands?

1062
01:09:39,880 --> 01:09:42,075
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

1063
01:09:42,880 --> 01:09:43,835
Right.

1064
01:09:58,120 --> 01:10:00,759
- Good night, old-timer.
- Eat shit.

1065
01:10:38,640 --> 01:10:40,232
What the hell is that?

1066
01:10:43,280 --> 01:10:45,748
There is an intruder
in Storage Facility B.

1067
01:10:45,880 --> 01:10:47,871
- <i>Attempted break-in in progress.</i>
- Son of a bitch!

1068
01:10:48,000 --> 01:10:50,275
<i>All security</i>
<i>to Storage Facility B.</i>

1069
01:12:10,480 --> 01:12:11,435
<i>Hey, Max.</i>

1070
01:12:14,240 --> 01:12:15,195
What's up?

1071
01:12:15,320 --> 01:12:17,117
Where are you?

1072
01:12:17,240 --> 01:12:19,549
Oh, I'm somewhere inside the ship.

1073
01:12:19,680 --> 01:12:22,797
Oh, yeah, me too.
Thanks, that helps a lot.

1074
01:12:22,920 --> 01:12:26,037
Max, did you say
you were <i>inside</i> the ship?

1075
01:12:26,840 --> 01:12:29,149
Yeah, it's amazing.

1076
01:12:29,280 --> 01:12:32,317
Hmm. Really?
What do you see?

1077
01:12:32,440 --> 01:12:36,069
<i>It's pretty dark.</i>
<i>I think I'm in the captain's quarters.</i>

1078
01:12:36,200 --> 01:12:37,713
That's interesting.

1079
01:12:43,200 --> 01:12:46,988
Max, suddenly I don't feel like
having an umbrella drink.

1080
01:12:58,760 --> 01:13:01,274
I'm beginning to think we're gonna
go home empty-handed.

1081
01:13:01,400 --> 01:13:03,709
Where are you, Max?
I'm gonna come hunt with you a while.

1082
01:13:03,840 --> 01:13:05,956
I'm coming to you.

1083
01:13:06,760 --> 01:13:09,479
How you see me?
I cut the red wire.

1084
01:13:09,600 --> 01:13:13,513
Ah, nice work, genius.
You cut the heating to the Jacuzzi.

1085
01:13:15,840 --> 01:13:18,195
<i>Max, you at the stern?</i>

1086
01:13:20,400 --> 01:13:21,549
<i>Max?</i>

1087
01:13:24,880 --> 01:13:27,314
<i>Stan Lloyd to Max Burdett.</i>
<i>Come in.</i>

1088
01:13:31,120 --> 01:13:33,509
Who'd he think he was,
the Invisible Man?

1089
01:13:36,480 --> 01:13:37,674
Dear God.

1090
01:13:37,800 --> 01:13:39,791
Shit.

1091
01:13:39,920 --> 01:13:41,876
It was a diversion.
Get back to the diamond!

1092
01:13:43,840 --> 01:13:45,671
<i>Max, where are you?</i>

1093
01:13:52,640 --> 01:13:54,039
<i>Will you answer me?</i>

1094
01:13:54,160 --> 01:13:55,354
<i>Hello!</i>

1095
01:13:55,480 --> 01:13:56,629
There!

1096
01:14:03,960 --> 01:14:06,315
He's in the vents!
He got the diamond!

1097
01:14:06,440 --> 01:14:07,998
Max, what was that?

1098
01:14:08,120 --> 01:14:09,678
<i>Max!</i>

1099
01:14:09,800 --> 01:14:11,518
I think he left his radio.

1100
01:14:11,640 --> 01:14:13,835
I thought I heard
something else.

1101
01:14:14,520 --> 01:14:16,715
<i>Where'd you go?</i>
<i>Is something wrong?</i>

1102
01:14:32,400 --> 01:14:34,197
Nice costume.

1103
01:14:35,520 --> 01:14:36,953
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

1104
01:14:38,600 --> 01:14:40,989
<i>Party all the time,</i>
<i>party all the time</i>

1105
01:14:41,120 --> 01:14:43,429
<i>Party all the time</i>

1106
01:14:43,560 --> 01:14:46,472
<i>My girl wants</i>
<i>to party all the time...</i>

1107
01:14:46,600 --> 01:14:48,909
Go back to your cabin, please.

1108
01:14:50,280 --> 01:14:52,157
Aha, there you are!

1109
01:14:52,360 --> 01:14:53,429
Hey, Max, come on.

1110
01:14:53,640 --> 01:14:55,631
Last night we were spooning.
Now you're running away?

1111
01:14:56,960 --> 01:14:58,313
<i>Come on!</i>

1112
01:14:58,960 --> 01:15:01,076
Yoo-hoo, Max.

1113
01:15:17,240 --> 01:15:20,038
Oh, I get it.
A little hide-and-seek.

1114
01:15:28,960 --> 01:15:31,872
Like I told you on the boat,
I caught 'em all.

1115
01:15:39,120 --> 01:15:41,634
You're good,
but you're not that good.

1116
01:15:47,040 --> 01:15:50,794
You know what they say--
the FBI always gets their man.

1117
01:15:54,160 --> 01:15:55,593
Max!

1118
01:15:55,720 --> 01:15:57,233
I'm having an air problem!

1119
01:15:58,360 --> 01:16:00,032
Stan, are you okay?

1120
01:16:00,160 --> 01:16:02,799
I can't breathe! Help!

1121
01:16:04,840 --> 01:16:06,114
Where are you, Stan?

1122
01:16:09,000 --> 01:16:10,513
I'm coming, Stan.

1123
01:16:10,640 --> 01:16:13,279
It's okay, Stan.
I'm right here.

1124
01:16:13,400 --> 01:16:14,515
Take off your mask.

1125
01:16:15,440 --> 01:16:16,475
I got him, honey.

1126
01:16:16,600 --> 01:16:18,033
I'm right here.

1127
01:16:19,120 --> 01:16:20,838
You're okay, Stan.

1128
01:16:23,120 --> 01:16:24,997
Nothing to worry about, partner.

1129
01:16:30,480 --> 01:16:33,074
I saw my life flash
before my eyes.

1130
01:16:33,280 --> 01:16:35,430
Leave it to me to get
the faulty regulator.

1131
01:16:35,600 --> 01:16:37,875
You know,
I never dove before.

1132
01:16:38,520 --> 01:16:41,432
- I would like to propose a toast.
- What are we celebrating?

1133
01:16:42,280 --> 01:16:43,235
Retirement.

1134
01:16:44,880 --> 01:16:46,359
- I'll drink to that.
- Good.

1135
01:16:50,400 --> 01:16:51,355
Hello.

1136
01:16:53,120 --> 01:16:54,314
What?

1137
01:16:54,440 --> 01:16:55,589
How?

1138
01:16:56,520 --> 01:16:58,511
- What's wrong?
- The diamond's been stolen.

1139
01:16:58,640 --> 01:17:01,313
- What?
- Half an hour ago.

1140
01:17:04,560 --> 01:17:05,549
You set us up.

1141
01:17:05,680 --> 01:17:06,795
Come on.

1142
01:17:06,920 --> 01:17:08,194
This whole thing.

1143
01:17:09,360 --> 01:17:12,079
You got your perfect alibi-- me.

1144
01:17:12,200 --> 01:17:13,838
Hey.

1145
01:17:13,960 --> 01:17:15,598
Get your hands up.

1146
01:17:15,720 --> 01:17:17,438
Are you serious?

1147
01:17:17,560 --> 01:17:19,118
No wonder you just retired.

1148
01:17:19,240 --> 01:17:22,232
You don't have
anything left to steal.

1149
01:17:22,360 --> 01:17:23,873
I've got to get to the ship.

1150
01:17:24,760 --> 01:17:25,909
You couldn't resist, could you?

1151
01:17:26,040 --> 01:17:27,951
You had to screw me
one last time.

1152
01:17:28,080 --> 01:17:30,514
You had to make an ass
out of me!

1153
01:17:37,840 --> 01:17:40,354
Hey, Lola.
Lola, wait.

1154
01:17:49,240 --> 01:17:50,195
Hey.

1155
01:17:54,600 --> 01:17:56,477
You really did save me down there.

1156
01:18:03,880 --> 01:18:07,316
I'm sorry I kept you in the dark.
I was only trying to protect you.

1157
01:18:07,440 --> 01:18:08,475
How generous of you.

1158
01:18:08,600 --> 01:18:10,955
You were right, you know.
I couldn't do it without you.

1159
01:18:11,080 --> 01:18:14,470
You gotta admit, though,
the look on Stan's face was sheer poetry.

1160
01:18:14,600 --> 01:18:16,113
Shut up, Max.

1161
01:18:16,240 --> 01:18:17,195
Hey.

1162
01:18:19,440 --> 01:18:20,589
Lola, please.

1163
01:18:21,680 --> 01:18:24,353
Max, I helped you
because I love you.

1164
01:18:24,480 --> 01:18:26,038
But now I'm leaving you.

1165
01:18:32,800 --> 01:18:35,598
Lola, I thought you'd
appreciate how I did it,

1166
01:18:35,720 --> 01:18:38,553
you of all people.
Hey, hey.

1167
01:18:40,880 --> 01:18:43,792
I do.
It was a smart plan, Max.

1168
01:18:43,920 --> 01:18:45,990
You're a great thief.

1169
01:18:46,920 --> 01:18:48,114
But I want a great man.

1170
01:18:54,880 --> 01:18:56,279
Lola.

1171
01:18:58,960 --> 01:19:00,109
Move inside.

1172
01:19:02,720 --> 01:19:05,109
What, you thought this was over?
Turn around!

1173
01:19:07,920 --> 01:19:10,195
I tried to deal with you
from an elevated place, man,

1174
01:19:10,320 --> 01:19:12,595
appeal to your intellect,
spit poetry and shit at you.

1175
01:19:12,720 --> 01:19:15,154
But no, man, you had to bring me
down to the gutter.

1176
01:19:15,280 --> 01:19:16,315
Where is the diamond?

1177
01:19:16,440 --> 01:19:18,954
- She's got nothing to do with this.
- Oh, she does now.

1178
01:19:19,080 --> 01:19:21,196
You kill my dog,
I'm gonna slay your cat.

1179
01:19:21,320 --> 01:19:22,548
Don't get--

1180
01:19:30,200 --> 01:19:31,269
Aah!

1181
01:19:32,200 --> 01:19:34,509
Nice throw, bitch!

1182
01:19:34,640 --> 01:19:36,073
No!

1183
01:19:41,760 --> 01:19:43,113
Where'd you come from?

1184
01:20:21,040 --> 01:20:23,713
He asked me to help him steal it
a week ago. I turned him down.

1185
01:20:23,840 --> 01:20:25,239
He must have stolen it himself,

1186
01:20:25,360 --> 01:20:28,113
then he came back here
to make sure there were no loose ends.

1187
01:20:28,240 --> 01:20:30,549
So why didn't you come to me,
tell me what they were planning?

1188
01:20:30,680 --> 01:20:32,113
He said he'd kill us.

1189
01:20:32,240 --> 01:20:33,832
You wouldn't have believed him anyway.

1190
01:20:33,960 --> 01:20:35,916
You thought Mooré was
the Second Coming for this island.

1191
01:20:36,040 --> 01:20:37,837
Don't tell me
what I think, woman.

1192
01:20:38,960 --> 01:20:41,190
- Where's the diamond?
- I have no idea.

1193
01:20:41,320 --> 01:20:44,232
- They were trying to frame us.
- Are we finished here?

1194
01:20:48,080 --> 01:20:50,514
You know, I don't believe a word
of what you're saying.

1195
01:20:51,280 --> 01:20:52,315
I know.

1196
01:21:09,840 --> 01:21:11,114
Don't leave.

1197
01:21:14,320 --> 01:21:15,719
Good luck, Max.

1198
01:22:36,840 --> 01:22:37,909
Lola, wait.

1199
01:22:38,480 --> 01:22:39,993
Hear me out.

1200
01:22:40,120 --> 01:22:42,998
It's not gonna work, Max.
Not this time.

1201
01:22:43,120 --> 01:22:46,351
I know it's too late,
but I finally wrote them. See?

1202
01:22:47,120 --> 01:22:48,235
Lots of words.

1203
01:22:48,360 --> 01:22:50,749
But I don't need to read them
because I know it by heart.

1204
01:22:51,720 --> 01:22:55,349
I've spent my whole life chasing things
which I thought were valuable,

1205
01:22:55,480 --> 01:22:58,631
when the only thing I really cared for
was right in front of me all along.

1206
01:23:01,000 --> 01:23:02,672
You are my heart, Lola.

1207
01:23:03,800 --> 01:23:06,314
From this moment on,
you are my only jewel.

1208
01:23:07,200 --> 01:23:09,839
I want a life
filled with sunsets.

1209
01:23:10,000 --> 01:23:13,390
And I never wanna watch
one of them without you, not ever.

1210
01:23:19,760 --> 01:23:21,830
The first diamond I've ever bought.

1211
01:23:25,120 --> 01:23:28,112
I love you, Lola Cirillo.

1212
01:23:30,000 --> 01:23:31,228
Marry me.

1213
01:23:41,440 --> 01:23:43,635
- On one condition.
- Anything.

1214
01:23:44,320 --> 01:23:45,673
I want the receipt.

1215
01:23:55,600 --> 01:23:56,555
Here you go, Luc.

1216
01:23:56,680 --> 01:23:58,113
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1217
01:23:58,240 --> 01:24:01,391
Jack on the rocks, with an umbrella.
What the hell, I'm celebrating.

1218
01:24:02,000 --> 01:24:04,673
Forget the Jack on the rocks,
let's have remoras all around.

1219
01:24:04,800 --> 01:24:06,199
Remoras all around.

1220
01:24:06,320 --> 01:24:08,550
Stanley, what the hell
are you doing here?

1221
01:24:08,680 --> 01:24:11,035
Well, I thought I'd stick around.

1222
01:24:12,760 --> 01:24:14,796
Oh, yeah, look familiar?

1223
01:24:14,920 --> 01:24:17,070
Treated myself,
maxed out the credit card.

1224
01:24:17,200 --> 01:24:18,679
But it suits me,
don't you think?

1225
01:24:18,800 --> 01:24:21,439
Well, it must take a bite
out of a government salary.

1226
01:24:21,560 --> 01:24:23,391
Ah, I can afford it all right.

1227
01:24:24,440 --> 01:24:27,159
Come on, let's sip
our remoras and talk, shall we?

1228
01:24:44,640 --> 01:24:46,437
I thought you said
these things have a kick.

1229
01:24:49,520 --> 01:24:51,033
Luc, what's in this?

1230
01:24:51,160 --> 01:24:54,197
Orange juice, mango juice,
grenadine, and coconut milk.

1231
01:24:55,840 --> 01:24:56,795
No liquor?

1232
01:25:00,440 --> 01:25:01,395
<i>Nada.</i>

1233
01:25:04,080 --> 01:25:06,310
I love these remoras!

1234
01:25:06,440 --> 01:25:08,271
Bartender, give me another!

1235
01:25:14,280 --> 01:25:16,475
You tell anyone I tucked him in,
I'll kill you.

1236
01:25:17,680 --> 01:25:20,274
- Sure thing, Mr. Burdett.
- Call me Max.

1237
01:25:20,400 --> 01:25:21,719
- Max.
- Okay.

1238
01:25:29,520 --> 01:25:32,592
You know,
I really like that cove.

1239
01:25:40,400 --> 01:25:42,994
Are you okay?
'Cause you don't look too good.

1240
01:25:47,120 --> 01:25:51,398
As an underwater enthusiast, you should
know what a remora really is, Max.

1241
01:25:51,520 --> 01:25:54,353
A remora is
kind of a stowaway,

1242
01:25:54,480 --> 01:25:58,792
a suckerfish that sticks
to the shark's body and feeds off it.

1243
01:25:58,920 --> 01:26:00,478
The shark does all the work,

1244
01:26:00,600 --> 01:26:03,558
but the remora gets the spoils.

1245
01:26:15,520 --> 01:26:16,669
You did it, Stan.

1246
01:26:19,480 --> 01:26:20,754
Right from the start.

1247
01:26:21,840 --> 01:26:24,035
It's the only one
you two haven't stolen.

1248
01:26:25,200 --> 01:26:26,519
You set me up.

1249
01:26:26,640 --> 01:26:29,234
I revel in it.
I revel in it!

1250
01:26:34,240 --> 01:26:37,869
Could it be that the great
Max Burdett has finally lost?

1251
01:26:41,960 --> 01:26:43,075
No, I didn't.

1252
01:26:45,040 --> 01:26:46,268
I got Lola.

1253
01:26:48,520 --> 01:26:49,999
Congratulations, Stan.

1254
01:26:58,240 --> 01:27:00,151
I'm looking at it right now.

1255
01:27:00,280 --> 01:27:02,748
My plane takes off
in ten minutes.

1256
01:27:02,880 --> 01:27:06,509
Tomorrow morning the bidding
will start at $30 million,

1257
01:27:06,640 --> 01:27:09,154
and if I were you,
I'd bring cash.

1258
